# Starting the App

When asked to start, launch, or run the app:

1. Run `./start.sh` from the project root (backgrounded with `block_until_ms: 0`)
2. Wait 5 seconds, then read the output to confirm all services started
3. Check for these success indicators:
   - Ollama: `âś“ Ollama already running` or `âś“ Ollama started`
   - Overlay: `âś“ Overlay started`
   - Backend: `âś“ Z Exp backend started (port 3030)`
4. If any service failed, read its log file:
   - Overlay: `/tmp/zexp-overlay.log` and `/tmp/zexp-overlay-build.log`
   - Backend: `/tmp/zexp-backend.log`

When asked to stop the app, run `./start.sh --kill`.

When asked to restart a specific service, run `./start.sh --restart <service>` where service is `overlay`, `backend`, or `ollama`.
